President Obama has announced additional members of the President's Advisory Council on Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships. The council is part of the White House Office of Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships and is composed of religious and secular leaders and scholars from different backgrounds. Each member is appointed to a one-year term. The council members include individuals such as Diane Baillargeon, President & CEO of Seedco, Bishop Charles Blake, Presiding Bishop of the Church of God in Christ, and Dr. Sharon Watkins, General Minister and President of the Christian Church (Disciples of Christ). The White House Office for Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships aims to be a resource for nonprofits and community organizations, both secular and faith-based, to make a bigger impact in their communities.